# Reelattice release checklist

When preparing a release (bump version, tag, or user asks to "ship"/"release"), complete **all** items before committing.

When **pushing app changes to `main`**, run this checklist and push the tag in the same session — see `reelattice-git-push.mdc`.

## Version numbers

Use **major.minor** in UI (`1.9`) and **major.minor.patch** in Rust/Tauri (`1.9.0`).

| File | Field |
|------|-------|
| `package.json` | `"version": "1.9"` |
| `src-tauri/Cargo.toml` | `version = "1.9.0"` |
| `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` | `"version": "1.9.0"` |
| `website/package.json` | `"version": "1.9.0"` |
| `website/src/lib/constants.ts` | `APP_VERSION = "1.9"` |

App display version comes from `CARGO_PKG_VERSION` in Rust — Cargo.toml must match `tauri.conf.json`.

## Release notes & user-facing copy

- [ ] `src/lib/changelog.ts` — new entry at top (newest first)
- [ ] `src/components/help-view.tsx` — if behavior changed for users
- [ ] `src/components/changelog-view.tsx` — intro copy if update flow changed

## Website (public marketing site)

Run the **Website check** in `reelattice-git-push.mdc` before every push — do not ship a tagged release without it.

- [ ] `website/package.json` + `website/src/lib/constants.ts` — `APP_VERSION` matches this release
- [ ] `website/src/lib/release-highlights.ts` — bullets match the top entry in `src/lib/changelog.ts`
- [ ] Hero, download, features, workflow — copy still accurate if the release changed user-facing behavior
- [ ] Legal / download URL — only if those changed

The website has no changelog page; version badges and marketing copy are the visitor-facing surface. In-app changelog remains the source of truth for release notes.

## Docs

- [ ] `docs/PLAN.md` — status line + new **Shipped (vX.Y)** section
- [ ] `docs/USER_GUIDE.md` — if user workflows, settings, or paths changed
- [ ] `README.md` — only if positioning, download link, or highlights changed materially

## Tag & publish

After commit + push to `main`:

```bash
git tag v1.9
git push origin v1.9
```

GitHub Actions builds the signed installer and `latest.json`. Do **not** tag without version bumps and changelog.

Vercel deploys `website/` from `main` on every push — complete the website checklist above in the same commit when shipping an app release.

See `reelattice-git-push.mdc` — changelog + **release tag** whenever `src/` or `src-tauri/` user-facing work ships on `main`.
